48GB RAM&lt;br&gt;
4x WD 2TB HDD (RAID 10) + 2x 120GB Intel SSD&lt;br&gt;
RAID: DELL H730 with BBU/cache

&lt;b&gt;Network details:&lt;/b&gt;

Main peerings are Magyar Telecom (including DTAG and other transits) and TeliaSonera HU. Exchanges include AMS-IX and BIX Budapest.

We have native IPv6 support! All virtual machines include a /64 IPv6 subnet free of charge. 

&lt;b&gt;DDoS protection details:&lt;/b&gt;

We have the capacity to mitigate attacks up to 80Gbps. Please do note that the guaranteed protection capacity is ~20Gbps. Attacks over the size are mitigated on a best effort basis. 

We can protect from all common forms on Layer 3 and 4. These could include UDP, spoofed forms (such as NTP, CHARGEN, SSDP etc), ICMP, SYN and various TCP types.

If an incoming attack exceeds the capacity available at a certain period, your /32 may be nullrouted automatically. Your IP will automatically be released within 20 minutes, unless the attack is still ongoing. Many factors account for the available capacity, depending on the source of the attack and the intensity. 

In example - If most of the attack is directed a single upstream, then the IP may be nullrouted at that particular upstream.


&lt;b&gt;Payment methods:&lt;/b&gt;
